.el .ds Aq '
.TH dkp-registry 1  "registry 0.2.0" 
.SH NAME
dkp\-registry \- Registry account and pack management (login, logout, keys, access)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdkp registry\fR [\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-\-audience\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Registry account and pack management (login, logout, keys, access)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR [default: plain]
Output format
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
plain: Human\-readable plain text (default)
.IP \(bu 2
table: Aligned table using comfy\-table
.IP \(bu 2
json: Pretty\-printed JSON
.RE
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress informational output; print only results
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Print debug info (schema paths, provider calls, etc.)
.TP
\fB\-\-audience\fR \fI<ID>\fR
Filter content to assets tagged for a specific audience profile
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
dkp\-registry\-register(1)
Create a new publisher account and save the API key to ~/.dkp/credentials
.TP
dkp\-registry\-login(1)
Authenticate with an existing account and save API key to ~/.dkp/credentials
.TP
dkp\-registry\-logout(1)
Remove saved credentials
.TP
dkp\-registry\-token(1)
Rotate your API key
.TP
dkp\-registry\-keys(1)
Manage Ed25519 public keys registered with the registry
.TP
dkp\-registry\-pack(1)
Pack\-level management subcommands
.SH VERSION
v0.2.0
